cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a method to improve the performance of DL CoMP in heterogeneous 5G NR networks.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed method is based on deep learning and online learning of non-linear interactions of features.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the throughput distribution in a wireless network.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses deep learning to construct a surrogate CoMP trigger function.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a method to enhance the performance of a wireless network through online learning.
